title: Frank Lloyd Wright Wooden Puzzle Set
description:
Our Frank Lloyd Wright® (American, 1867–1959) puzzle set is perfect for your next puzzling party.
Choose from 6 designs featuring patterns from March Balloons, a design adapted from a series of 12 abstracts Wright created for the covers of Liberty Magazine from 1926 to 1928 and Tree of Life art glass window which can be found in the Darwin D. Martin house in Buffalo, NY (1904).
Puzzles are packaged in a wooden box with a sliding back.

Puzzle Box: 11 x 6 x 1 1/2 in.
Individual Puzzles: 5 in. sq.
